{
  "texts": [
    "If p i is the probability of having a CGW of S /N > 3 in the ith bin, we can compute the probability of detecting at least one CGW with S /N > 3 in DR2new according to these models as p = 1 -(1p i), which gives p = 0.49.",
    "It is therefore quite possible that the This probability is obviously S/N threshold dependent.",
    "For example, by increasing this threshold to S /N > 5, we get p = 0.13.",
    "This is comparable to the 6% chance found by Bécsy et al. (2022).",
    "and the slightly larger probability in our models is likely due to the louder overall amplitudes of the signals considered here."
  ]
}